{"moduleCode":"MS1102E","title":"Understanding the Contemporary Malay World","description":"This is an introduction to studies on Malays and Malayness within countries in the Malay-Indonesian archipelago. The main question will be of conflict, change and continuity. Approaches in studying these responses will include topics on colonialism and the decolonisation of ideas, the interrogation of Malayness, development and political economy, Islam and its institutions, arts and literary aesthetics, gender, family and community, and state and Malay society in contemporary Singapore and the region.","moduleCredit":4.0,"department":"Malay Studies","faculty":"Arts and Social Science","preclusion":"MS1101E","acadYear":"2021/2022","attributes":{"mpes1":true,"mpes2":true,"su":true},"semesterData":[{"semester":1,"examDuration":0,"timetable":[{"classNo":"E2","startTime":1600,"endTime":1800,"venue":"E-Learn_C","day":"Monday","lessonType":"Tutorial","size":25},{"classNo":"1","startTime":1400,"endTime":1600,"venue":"E-Learn_C","day":"Tuesday","lessonType":"Lecture","size":100},{"classNo":"E1","startTime":1000,"endTime":1200,"venue":"E-Learn_C","day":"Monday","lessonType":"Tutorial","size":25},{"classNo":"E3","startTime":1600,"endTime":1800,"venue":"E-Learn_C","day":"Tuesday","lessonType":"Tutorial","size":25}]},{"semester":2,"examDuration":0,"timetable":[{"classNo":"1","startTime":1600,"endTime":1800,"venue":"LT14","day":"Monday","lessonType":"Lecture","size":100},{"classNo":"E3","startTime":1600,"endTime":1800,"venue":"AS4-0602","day":"Thursday","lessonType":"Tutorial","size":25},{"classNo":"E2","startTime":1000,"endTime":1200,"venue":"AS3-0214","day":"Tuesday","lessonType":"Tutorial","size":25},{"classNo":"E4","startTime":1000,"endTime":1200,"venue":"AS4-0114","day":"Friday","lessonType":"Tutorial","size":25},{"classNo":"E1","startTime":800,"endTime":1000,"venue":"AS3-0214","day":"Monday","lessonType":"Tutorial","size":25}]}]}